<subSubSection id="3180654FFF92C107F9EFFCD2FD6536D1" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="792536C4FF92C107F9EFFCD2FE8B3663" blockId="13.[189,324,859,885]" box="[189,324,859,885]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading id="226D81A8FF92C107F9EFFCD2FE8B3663" bold="true" box="[189,324,859,885]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF92C107F9EFFCD2FE8B3663" bold="true" box="[189,324,859,885]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF92C107F9EFFC03FD6536D1" blockId="13.[189,1399,906,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The name of the new species, 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF92C107FB7FFC02FD1736B2" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[557,728,906,932]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF92C107FB7FFC02FD1736B2" box="[557,728,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Marcusia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comes from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF92C107FAAFFC03FBF236B2" box="[1021,1085,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">albus</emphasis>
’ (white), and refers to the ivory white coloration this species shows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
