<subSubSection id="3180654FFF92C104F9EFFAD9FAEA347F" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="792536C4FF92C107F9EFFAD9FE81307C" blockId="13.[189,334,1360,1386]" box="[189,334,1360,1386]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading id="226D81A8FF92C107F9EFFAD9FE81307C" bold="true" box="[189,334,1360,1386]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF92C107F9EFFAD9FE81307C" bold="true" box="[189,334,1360,1386]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF92C107F9EFFAF6FE5833A4" blockId="13.[188,1400,1406,1714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
BODY. Shape oval. Length 
<quantity id="BE629B21FF92C107F8A1FAF7FD8A308F" box="[499,581,1406,1433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="cm" value="2.6">2.6 cm</quantity>
. Smooth dorsal surface. Background pigmentation ivory white, darker along the middle dorsal region of the body. Amber dots and thin brushstroke-like lines garnish the dorsal surface. A thin, dark stripe, sometimes interrupted, extends along the central dorsal line (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107FD9DFA4CFAE230C9" box="[1231,1325,1477,1503]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Two delicate marginal folds, separate and pointed, could be interpreted as pseudotentacles. Tentacular eyes scarce and widely dispersed over the tentacles. Cerebral eyes anterior drop-shaped and crossed by the central midline. Marginal eyes only at the anterior part (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107FA03F9A7FC63335E" box="[849,940,1582,1608]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Ruffled pharynx, in the middle of the body with a central oral pore. Ventral sucker at the posterior part of the body. Male and female genital pore lead in a common genital atrium (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107FBCFF9FCFD2A3399" box="[669,741,1653,1679]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D–E) that opens in the posterior body region after the pharynx (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107F87FF911FE4533A4" box="[301,394,1688,1714]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF92C107F9EFF953FB843296" blockId="13.[189,1400,1753,1921]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
MALE REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM. Male copulatory organ backwards oriented, with a muscular penis papilla, very muscular seminal vesicle (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107FB64F975FD7C3201" box="[566,691,1788,1815]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2C, E</figureCitation>
) and without a prostatic vesicle, instead a simple glandular epithelium leads into the penis papilla (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF92C107FBDDF8A9FD1A322C" box="[655,725,1824,1850]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D–E). Seminal vesicle rounded, frontal oriented and with thick muscular walls, opening into the ejaculatory duct. Short ejaculatory duct opens into the penis papillae. The male atrium is small and thin, connected to the common atrium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF91C104F9EFFE80FAEA347F" blockId="14.[189,1398,265,362]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
FEMALE REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM (
<figureCitation id="E1A12A41FF91C104FB61FE80FD743435" box="[563,699,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" captionTargetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-123@14.[189,1399,602,1817]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 2. Marcusia alba sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683).A. Whole live animal, dorsal view.B. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). C. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. D. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. E. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 2C, E</figureCitation>
). The vagina runs from the common genital atrium and continues dorsally into a narrowed duct that widens into a chamber, the cement pouch. The vagina continues dorsally, then curves posteriorly and ventrally and ends with the entry of the oviducts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3180654FFF91C105F9EFFE18FC44363C" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="792536C4FF91C104F9EFFE18FEE034BD" blockId="14.[189,303,401,427]" box="[189,303,401,427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading id="226D81A8FF91C104F9EFFE18FEE034BD" bold="true" box="[189,303,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104F9EFFE18FEE034BD" bold="true" box="[189,303,401,427]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF91C104F9EFFE49FB943736" blockId="14.[189,1398,447,544]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF91C104F9EFFE49FEA334CF" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,364,447,473]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104F9EFFE49FEA334CF" box="[189,364,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Marcusia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF91C104F825FE49FE1934CC" box="[375,470,448,474]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF91C104FBBBFE49FC9734CF" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[745,856,448,473]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104FBBBFE49FC9734CF" box="[745,856,448,473]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Marcusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of cerebral, frontal and marginal eyes, male copulatory organ enclosed in a muscular bulb, the absence of prostatic vesicle and the common male and female atrium genital, as well as the common gonopore.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2DE5664CFF91C104F9EFF8B7FEE732F3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561531" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4561531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561531/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" startId="14.[189,232,1854,1880]" targetBox="[214,1379,612,1805]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="792536C4FF91C104F9EFF8B7FEE732F3" blockId="14.[185,1398,1854,2021]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104F9EFF8B7FEC7324E" bold="true" box="[189,264,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF91C104F85FF8B6FE7A324E" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[269,437,1854,1880]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104F85FF8B6FE7A324E" box="[269,437,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Marcusia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF91C104F8E8F8B7FDDD324E" box="[442,530,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(MNCN 4.01/2620 to 2683). 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104FA30F8B7FCB8324E" bold="true" box="[866,887,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">A</emphasis>
. Whole live animal, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104FDA0F8B7FAC9324E" bold="true" box="[1266,1286,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and pseudotentacles (white arrows). 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104FAB0F8E8FC38326D" bold="true" box="[994,1015,1889,1915]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">C</emphasis>
. Histological section of the male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104FBDCF80DFD6E3288" bold="true" box="[654,673,1924,1950]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D</emphasis>
. Histological section of the female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. 
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF91C104F833F821FEBD32D4" bold="true" box="[353,370,1960,1986]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E</emphasis>
. Sagittal reconstruction of the reproduction system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF90C105F9EFFE80FB4A34C5" blockId="15.[189,1399,265,467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105F81AFE83FE783435" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[328,439,266,291]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105F81AFE83FE783435" box="[328,439,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contained only one species, 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FA73FE83FB6F3432" authority="Hyman, 1953" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[801,1184,265,292]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FA73FE83FC223435" box="[801,1005,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia ernesti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1D0B4B35FF90C105FAABFE80FB6F3432" author="Hyman LH" box="[1017,1184,265,292]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="269 - 391" refId="ref17483" refString="Hyman LH. 1953. The polyclad flatworms of the Pacific coast of North America. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 100: 269 - 391. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1028 [accessed 28 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1953">Hyman, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, known from the coast of the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="BB5EF826FF90C105F8E8FEA5FDFE3450" box="[442,561,300,326]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">California</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1D0B4B35FF90C105FB11FEA5FD2A3451" author="Hyman LH" box="[579,741,300,327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="269 - 391" refId="ref17483" refString="Hyman LH. 1953. The polyclad flatworms of the Pacific coast of North America. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 100: 269 - 391. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1028 [accessed 28 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1953">Hyman 1953</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FBAFFEA4FC083450" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[765,967,301,326]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FBAFFEA4FC083450" box="[765,967,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia ernesti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FD54FEA4FBAA3450" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[1030,1125,300,326]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FD54FEA4FBAA3450" box="[1030,1125,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF90C105FD22FEA4FB013451" box="[1136,1230,301,327]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished by their coloration patterns. 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FBE6FED9FCB3347F" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[692,892,336,361]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FBE6FED9FCB3347F" box="[692,892,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia ernesti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is black or grey with darker splotches and dotted with white spots, only visible in preserved individuals after 
<bibRefCitation id="1D0B4B35FF90C105FA8EFEFAFB42349B" author="Hyman LH" box="[988,1165,370,397]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="269 - 391" refId="ref17483" refString="Hyman LH. 1953. The polyclad flatworms of the Pacific coast of North America. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 100: 269 - 391. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1028 [accessed 28 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1953">Hyman (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FDC8FEFAFB38349A" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[1178,1271,370,396]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FDC8FEFAFB38349A" box="[1178,1271,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF90C105FDACFEFAFA95349B" box="[1278,1370,371,397]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is ivory white with brownish dots and stripes. The penis papilla is spherical in 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FD7CFE1EFB4634A6" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[1070,1161,406,432]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FD7CFE1EFB4634A6" box="[1070,1161,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and elongated in 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FC04FE1EFEC234C5" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FC04FE1EFEC234C5" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. ernesti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the male atrium being tube-like and longer in the Californian species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF90C105F9EFFE73FE633768" blockId="15.[189,1400,506,639]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Another difference lies in the eyes’ presence and distribution. 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FA91FE72FB413702" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[963,1166,507,532]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FA91FE72FB413702" box="[963,1166,507,532]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia ernesti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents marginal, frontal and cerebral eyes as well as two characteristic eye clusters with diagnostic value (
<bibRefCitation id="1D0B4B35FF90C105FD9EFD97FAA5372E" author="Hyman LH" box="[1228,1386,541,568]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="269 - 391" refId="ref17483" refString="Hyman LH. 1953. The polyclad flatworms of the Pacific coast of North America. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 100: 269 - 391. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1028 [accessed 28 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1953">Hyman 1953</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105F9EFFDCBFEA5374D" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,362,577,603]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105F9EFFDCBFEA5374D" box="[189,362,577,603]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF90C105F827FDC8FE1A374D" box="[373,469,577,603]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, on the other hand, has cerebral, marginal and tentacular eyes, but not frontal eyes or eye clusters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="792536C4FF90C105F9EFFD2CFC44363C" blockId="15.[189,1399,677,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The differences listed are enough to consider 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FBB2FD2FFC9637A9" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[736,857,678,703]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FBB2FD2FFC9637A9" box="[736,857,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. ernesti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FAC7FD2FFC3D37A9" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[917,1010,677,703]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FAC7FD2FFC3D37A9" box="[917,1010,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF90C105FAABFD2FFB9937D6" box="[1017,1110,678,704]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as two different species of the same genus. Furthermore, the molecular analyses show the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FD4FFD40FB4337F4" authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[1053,1164,713,738]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FD4FFD40FB4337F4" box="[1053,1164,713,738]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(represented in this case by 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105F84EFD64FE083610" authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[284,455,748,774]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Cryptocelidae" genus="Marcusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="alba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105F84EFD64FE083610" box="[284,455,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Marcusia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="50DD57ADFF90C105F89DFD65FDE43610" box="[463,555,748,774]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) as a genus closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105FADFFD65FB6B3610" authority="Laidlaw, 1902" authorityName="Laidlaw" authorityYear="1902" box="[909,1188,748,774]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BEEEAD6FF90C105FADFFD65FC3A3610" box="[909,1013,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Pericelis</emphasis>
Laidlaw, 1902
</taxonomicName>
within the family 
<taxonomicName id="BE9A4D47FF90C105F9EFFC86FE2B363F" authority="Lang, 1884" authorityName="Lang" authorityYear="1884" box="[189,484,783,810]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Anonymidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">
Anonymidae 
<bibRefCitation id="1D0B4B35FF90C105F80EFC99FE2B363F" author="Lang A." box="[348,484,783,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref18146" refString="Lang A. 1884. Die Polycladen (Seeplanarien) des Golfes von Neapel und der angrenzenden Meeresabschnitte. Eine Monographie. Fauna und Flora des Golfes von Neapel 11. Engelmann, Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10545" type="book" year="1884">Lang, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but as a clearly independent genus.
</paragraph>
